inks the real `but-agentlog` crate.\n+6. **Projection contract.** Define the server-facing output from\n+   `but-agentlog`: related sessions, related turns, record previews, exact\n+   drill-down, relevance evidence, and redaction guarantees.\n+7. **PR-to-target resolution.** Define how a pull request maps to branch,\n+   review, or change targets that `but-agentlog` can query.\n+8. **Session selection and ranking.** Decide which related sessions appear by\n+   default, how turns are highlighted, and how the UI explains relevance without\n+   claiming authorship.\n+9. **Session browsing UX.** Lock the first-page structure: overview, sessions,\n+   turn timeline, grouped records, validation, open questions, and raw evidence\n+   drawer.\n+10. **Failure states.** Define what the page shows for no access, no captured\n+    data, weak relation evidence, redaction failures, too much data, and stale\n+    GitMeta.\n+11. **Retention and caching.** Decide whether generated trails are stored,\n+    invalidated, expired, or rebuilt on demand.\n+12. **Out-of-scope line.** Explicitly exclude compliance/audit guarantees,\n+    full transcript publishing by default, automatic private publication, and\n+    model-generated summaries as the source of truth.\n+\n+The smallest buildable slice should prove the full path without solving every\n+future policy:\n+\n+```text\n+GitHub PR URL -> access check -> but-agentlog lookup -> review-safe projection\n+-> overview page -> session/turn drill-down\n+```\n+\n+If that path is vague, implementation should wait.\n \n ## Implementation Boundary\n \n Keep the primitive crate boring.\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T14:24:59.028Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}